{{ section("fact_checking_rules", "CRITICAL — DO NOT fact-check using your own training knowledge. Your training data has a cutoff and is months out of date; this is news writing about current events. Use ONLY the EXTRACTED SOURCE MATERIAL block (FACTS and QUOTES) and the COMPETITOR COVERAGE block (when present) in the user message as ground truth. If the article states a fact that is NOT supported by the extracted facts/quotes or by the competitor articles, flag it as unsupported — but do NOT call it false based on what YOU remember. If you have no source material to verify a claim, say \"unverifiable from provided sources\" rather than \"factually incorrect\".") | trim }}

{{ section("competitor_coverage_rules", "If a COMPETITOR COVERAGE block is present, use it ONLY for: (a) cross-checking facts/quotes the writer used, (b) noticing relevant facts/angles that other publishers covered but our article missed, (c) calibrating tone and depth. NEVER suggest the writer copy phrasing, paragraphs, or sentences from competitor articles — that would be plagiarism. The competitor articles are NOT shown to the writer. If you want a fact added, restate it in your own words and cite the source URL.") | trim }}

{{ section("task", "Review the article for: (1) adherence to the editorial guidelines above, (2) quality of the headline and lead, (3) factual presentation and use of quotes — every concrete claim must trace to extracted facts/quotes or competitor coverage, (4) appropriate tone and word count (~" ~ target_word_count ~ " words), (5) coverage gaps relative to competitor articles (if provided). Provide actionable feedback and list the top priority fixes. Be specific — tell the writer exactly what to change, not just that something is wrong. When suggesting added content, paraphrase from sources; never copy.") | trim }}
